Set Up Case Merge in Lightning Experience

Enable the Case Merge setting. Add the Merge Cases action to the case record home and add the Merge Cases button to the case list view.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
Manage Cases AND Customize Application

Case Merge limitations:
You can't merge cases pending in an Omni-Channel queue or assigned to agents with Opened or Assigned status.
You can't undo a merge.
The Compare Cases window shows only the first 35 lookup fields that were added to the case page layout.

To enable Case Merge: From Setup, enter Case Merge in the Quick Find box, then select Case Merge. Toggle Merge Cases to proceed to Case Merge settings.

Specify how to deal with duplicate cases:
Select Delete duplicate cases after merge to delete the source files after they're merged.
Assign a status value for your merged cases if you choose to keep your duplicate cases after the merge.
Add a Merged Cases related list to your Case home page.
title: Set Up Case Merge in Lightning Experience
